data.body:

There was a discussion to modify the pool contract so as to remove the activation queue as discussed in [SWIP-8]. The topic has been discussed in the forum with 12 out of 12 votes passing and the topic was open for discussion over three weeks.

[Note: The previous snapshot referenced an incorrect function setPendingValidatorsLimit. This snapshot now lists the correct function. I propose to execute the specification to modify the pool contract to remove the activation queue.

data.title: Approve addition of Community Oracle
data.body:
Discussion about this snapshot: https://forum.stakewise.io/t/dao-vote-approve-addition-of-community-oracle/665

Introduction

The community desires to get involved in the StakeWise ecosystem.  A way of showing support to the StakeWise ecosystem is to host a community supported oracle capable of voting on distribution rewards and validator additions.

As a result, the community oracle server has been running for the past three weeks, regularly submitting unofficial votes for rewards distribution and adding validators for the pool.  The server is run by Brian Childers (Discord Handle: Red.Beard (brianchilders) / Twitter Handle: brianchilders), and is running the latest version of the oracle software provided by StakeWise.  The server will be maintained and kept up to date: software and hardware.

Server Specs:

/proc/cpuinfo
model name    : AMD Ryzen 5 3400G with Radeon Vega Graphics
cpu cores    : 4

/proc/meminfo
MemTotal:       65798884 kB

df -h
/dev/sda2       457G  134G  301G  31% /

uname -a
Linux isaac 5.13.0-30-generic #33~20.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Mon Feb 7 14:25:10 UTC 2022 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux

In addition, Brian has released a community StakeWise oracle monitoring page, located at https://launchpad.eatsteakbewise.com/oraclestatus.html which will help drive transparency regarding the performance of all StakeWise oracles.

I propose to execute the specification to modify the oracle contract to add the community oracle to the list of authorized oracles allowed to submit official votes for distributor, total rewards and validators on mainnet.

Specification

DAO calls addOracle function of Oracle contract with the following parameter:

account: 0x27fdcb0b45b0991595BF4A8bECd43E1d8eB8E7d3

data.title: Extend StakeWise Labs operator with 200 keys
data.body:
Discussion about this Snapshot: https://forum.stakewise.io/t/extend-stakewise-labs-operator-with-200-keys/615

## Introduction
While the core team is finalizing the last missing parts to start onboarding new operators, we need to have some allocation of the validator keys for the existing ether to start staking.

Extend the only node operator in the network, Stakewise Labs, with 200 more keys for the deposited ether to start staking.

## Specification

- DAO calls `addOperator` function of `PoolValidators` contract with the following parameters:
    * operator: `0x5fc60576B92c5cE5c341C43e3B2866eb9E0cdDD1`
    * depositDataMerkleRoot: `0x6f7be760fb7bf7160300dde3214e2de28c9a4e409a15897d8cb3e1f1b7635d14`
    * depositDataMerkleProofs: `/ipfs/QmZEhxAhp4ymeoNZ6L3wdM2pxCAo9R8MJ8aa7hDG7Km3ZZ`

- If the proposal will be approved, the operator must perform the following steps:
    * Call `operator-cli sync-vault` or `operator-cli sync-local` with the same mnemonic as used for generating the proposal
    * Create or update validators and make sure the new keys are added
    * Call `commitOperator` from the `0x5fc60576B92c5cE5c341C43e3B2866eb9E0cdDD1` address

data.title: StakeWise V2 Upgrade
data.body:
Discussions about the snapshot are at https://forum.stakewise.io/t/554

Upgrade StakeWise smart contracts to the V2 release. The V2 features can be looked up at https://medium.com/@stakewise/a-new-era-for-stakewise-upgrading-to-a-decentralized-architecture-e598fde75ea8

The upgrade changes the implementation contracts for some of the existing contracts and initializes them:

## Pool Contract
1. Pause contract
2. Change implementation address to [0xe68E649862F7036094f1E4eD5d69a738aCDE666f](https://etherscan.io/address/0xe68E649862F7036094f1E4eD5d69a738aCDE666f)
3. Change Oracles address to [0x8a887282E67ff41d36C0b7537eAB035291461AcD](https://etherscan.io/address/0x8a887282E67ff41d36C0b7537eAB035291461AcD) by calling upgrade function
4. Change PoolValidators address to [0x002932e11E95DC84C17ed5f94a0439645D8a97BC](https://etherscan.io/address/0x002932e11E95DC84C17ed5f94a0439645D8a97BC) by calling upgrade function
5. Unpause contract

## RewardEthToken Contract
1. Pause contract
2. Change implementation address to [0x7cA75ccf264b2d9F91D4ABA7639fC7FcC73a7e09](https://etherscan.io/address/0x7cA75ccf264b2d9F91D4ABA7639fC7FcC73a7e09)
3. Change Oracles address to [0x8a887282E67ff41d36C0b7537eAB035291461AcD](https://etherscan.io/address/0x8a887282E67ff41d36C0b7537eAB035291461AcD) by calling upgrade function
4. Unpause contract

## MerkleDistributor Contract
1. Pause contract
2. Change implementation address to [0x1d873651c38D912c8A7E1eBfB013Aa96bE5AACBC](https://etherscan.io/address/0x1d873651c38D912c8A7E1eBfB013Aa96bE5AACBC)
3. Change Oracles address to [0x8a887282E67ff41d36C0b7537eAB035291461AcD](https://etherscan.io/address/0x8a887282E67ff41d36C0b7537eAB035291461AcD) by calling upgrade function

data.title: [SWIP-2] Refund the farming incentives committed by the Future Fund towards the original $SWISE/$1INCH LM campaign
data.body:
A few weeks back, the team contributed 2,000,000 $SWISE (0.2% of the supply) from the Future Fund towards a farming campaign in the $SWISE/$1INCH liquidity pool. Following some initial community feedback to the idea of bootstrapping liquidity in this fashion, we would like to present SWIP-2 up for the community vote.

This SWIP will ask the forum members to vote on whether the amount of tokens that was used for seeding the 1st farming campaign with 1inch (2,000,000 $SWISE) should be refunded to the Future Fund from the Treasury, considering it is a better source for such disbursals.

# Motivation

As was previously outlined in the unofficial proposal 3, the farming campaign was meant to bootstrap the initial liquidity in the $SWISE token in order to achieve price discovery and decentralize ownership beyond just the airdrop participants. The chosen amount (2,000,000 $SWISE) was believed to strike a good balance between a sufficiently good incentive to offer liquidity and not overpaying for price discovery and decentralization. The team needed to act quickly and so made a choice to commit the said amount of $SWISE from the Future Fund, instead of a lengthier process of initiating a public quorum to disburse the tokens from the DAO Treasury.

Given the circumstances, the team proposes that a refund of said 2,000,000 $SWISE be made to the Future Fund from the DAO Treasury. The rationale is simple: 1) by design, the Treasury is a better source of tokens for the liquidity mining incentives, and 2) drawing from the Future Fund for liquidity mining incentives means less funding would be raised in the future, limiting the development runway. If this SWIP is approved, the funds in the Treasury would be put to their intended use, and the Future Fund would be replenished to support the future fundraising activity.

# Specification

If the proposal is approved, the StakeWise DAO Governance multisig would submit one transaction for a transfer of 2,000,000 $SWISE from the DAO Treasury to the Future Funds wallet. The link to a Snapshot Vote specifying the transaction for the transfer will later be published in this thread.

# Verify transfer transaction

The transfer transaction has been attached to this snapshot:

- Target address is set to [SWISE Token](https://etherscan.io/token/0x48c3399719b582dd63eb5aadf12a40b4c3f52fa2) - the desired token to send
- Value is set to `0.0 ETH` - no Ether will be transferred with the transaction
- Data is correctly formed:

  - Go to [Hashex](https://abi.hashex.org/) and paste the [ERC-20 Contract ABI](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/stakewise/contracts/master/abi/IERC20Upgradeable.json)
  - Set **function type** to **transfer**
  - Set **recipient** to [StakeWise Future Fund](https://etherscan.io/address/0xf91AA4a655B6F43243ed4C2853F3508314DaA2aB) address
  - Set amount to `2000000000000000000000000` which is `2,000,000` SWISE with 18 decimals.

  The received `data` should be equal to the one attached to the transaction.
data.author: 0x7F910AE96d839e96c265bD479d35EaC25dDc072E

data.title: [SWIP-1] Extend the liquidity mining campaign for the $SWISE / $1INCH pool
data.body:
A few weeks back, we set up the first liquidity pool for $SWISE, pairing it with the $1INCH token and listing on 1inch. This was done to take advantage of the opportunity for a joint liquidity mining program with the 1inch Exchange. As the original program approaches its end (May 25th is the last day), the StakeWise team would like to propose to extend the liquidity mining campaign in the $SWISE/$1INCH pool until the 25th of June and allocate 1,000,000 $SWISE towards farming rewards from the DAO Treasury.

# Motivation

The 1inch pool remains a key trading venue for $SWISE until the liquidity pools with other pairs like $SWISE/ETH and $SWISE/USDC are deployed and $SWISE staking is rolled out. Extending the farming campaign would help StakeWise preserve good liquidity in the pool, which is necessary for price stability, and offer an additional incentive to hold $SWISE until other functionality for it is deployed.

# To summarize:

$SWISE holders can put their capital to good use, earning more $SWISE (and trading fees)
More $SWISE is deployed as liquidity instead of inactively sitting in the wallet or being sold
Deeper liquidity leads to a more stable $SWISE price
Outsiders and $1INCH holders who want to generate yield will buy $SWISE to LP, boosting $SWISE and contributing more liquidity
Allocating 1,000,000 $SWISE towards the new campaign is believed to offer a worthwhile incentive (~45% APY at the current amount of value locked) to provide liquidity given the opportunity cost of deploying capital.

# Specification

If the proposal is approved, we would submit one transaction for a transfer of 1,000,000 $SWISE from the DAO Treasury (0x144a98cb1CdBb23610501fE6108858D9B7D24934) to the 1inch farming rewards contract (0x2CB9e71A5cf989008Ba93dAD8EdB988eC1b4182f).
